  "body": "I'm trying to render a dynamic element, using props as the element type:\n\n``` javascript\n<Text elem={React.DOM.textarea}/>\n```\n\nThe 'Text' component:\n\n``` javascript\n  render() {\n    const { elem } = this.props \n    return (\n      <div className={Style.container}>\n        <elem className={Style.text} defaultValue={'test'}></elem>\n      </div>\n    )\n  }\n```\n\nThis worked in older versions of react, however now it doesn't. For this example I'm getting: \nInvariant Violation: If you supply `defaultValue` on a <textarea>, do not pass children.\n\nI'm using 0.14.0-rc1 with react-dom, react-router and isomorphic. If there's a better way to handle this please let me know!\n",
